    The average male height in the U.S. by race is: Non-Hispanic white: 177.4 centimeters, or just under 5 feet, 10 inches. Non-Hispanic black: 175.5 centimeters, or just over 5 feet, 9 inches. Non-Hispanic Asian: 169.7 centimeters, or just under 5 feet, 7 inches.23 Aug 2024
